AWS WALLY 1.0

1. Get apache user from /etc/apache/httpd.conf

2. /etc/sudoers

Replace wwwrun below with your apache user and paste in /etc/sudoers

wwwrun	ALL=(ALL) NOPASSWD: /usr/sbin/iptables-save
wwwrun	ALL=(ALL) NOPASSWD: /usr/sbin/iptables-restore
wwwrun	ALL=(ALL) NOPASSWD: /usr/sbin/iptables

3. defaults.php

Replace constants bellow with the values in your system (full path to iptables, iptables-save, iptables-xml and iptables-restore binaries)

AWS_WALLY_IPTABLES
AWS_WALLY_IPTABLES_SAVE
AWS_WALLY_IPTABLES_RESTORE
AWS_WALLY_IPTABLES_XML

Set user and password for Designer:

AWS_DESIGNER_ADMIN
AWS_DESIGNER_PASSWORD